### 📈 2. Cross-Checked Visual Analytics Queries (`analytics.sql`)

These queries reverse-engineer the computational functions built inside your `SentimentRadarApp` layout class. Running these scripts on your SQL database will return the exact calculations displayed on your interface canvas:

#### Query A: Donut Chart Distribution Data (`_draw_donut`)

Replicates the matching matrix for your pie distribution wedges based on your hardcoded boundaries (`score >= 15` and `score <= -15`):

```sql
SELECT 
    sentiment_label,
    COUNT(*) as item_count,
    ROUND(COUNT(*) / (SELECT COUNT(*) FROM market_feeds WHERE source_category = 'Global Markets') * 100, 1) as distribution_percentage
FROM market_feeds
WHERE source_category = 'Global Markets' -- Dynamically matches your drop-down choice
GROUP BY sentiment_label;

```

#### Query B: Chronological Historical Trajectory Data (`_draw_trend`)

Replicates your rolling historical tracking array (`self.history`) by taking daily aggregated rolling mean averages across active trading horizons:

```sql
SELECT 
    SUBSTRING_INDEX(published_txt, ',', 1) as formatted_date, -- Isolates date from your custom text string
    ROUND(AVG(sentiment_score), 1) as average_sentiment_score,
    COUNT(*) as total_headlines_parsed
FROM market_feeds
GROUP BY SUBSTRING_INDEX(published_txt, ',', 1)
ORDER BY STR_TO_DATE(SUBSTRING_INDEX(published_txt, ',', 1), '%d %b %Y') DESC
LIMIT 18; -- Matches your application's absolute layout history storage window buffer

```

#### Query C: Volumetric Pressure Matrix (`_draw_pressure`)

Mimics the positive, negative, and localized neutral multi-directional coordinate scaling weights required to compute your horizontal volumetric metrics chart canvas:

```sql
SELECT 
    SUM(CASE WHEN sentiment_score > 0 THEN sentiment_score ELSE 0 END) as bullish_accumulated_pressure,
    SUM(CASE WHEN sentiment_score BETWEEN -14.9 AND 14.9 THEN 12 ELSE 0 END) as neutral_accumulated_pressure, -- Blends your 12-point scaling multiplier
    SUM(CASE WHEN sentiment_score < 0 THEN ABS(sentiment_score) ELSE 0 END) as bearish_accumulated_pressure
FROM market_feeds
WHERE source_category = 'Indian Markets';

```

#### Query D: Policy Stance Aggregator (`_update_policy_footer`)

Replicates the primary regulatory macro check script used to output your footer metrics bar. It tracks individual classification counts while fetching the modal average stance via SQL grouping:

```sql
SELECT 
    policy_mood as dominant_stance,
    COUNT(*) as stance_occurrence_count,
    ROUND(AVG(policy_confidence), 0) as average_engine_confidence_percentage
FROM market_feeds
WHERE source_category = 'RBI/SEBI Releases'
GROUP BY policy_mood
ORDER BY stance_occurrence_count DESC; -- Top returned record reflects your code's max(set(moods)) calculation

```
